NEC 2023 Table 400.4 - Flexible Cords and Flexible Cables
Section: Article 400
Description: Comprehensive list of all NEC-recognized flexible cord and cable types with specifications. Over 90 cord types from lamp cord (Type C) to portable power cable (Type W). Details voltage ratings (300V-2000V), wire sizes, conductor counts, insulation types (thermoset/thermoplastic/elastomer), jacket materials, and usage categories (hard usage, extra-hard usage, pendant, portable). Includes specialty cords: electric vehicle (EV/EVT), elevator (E/EO), heater (HPD/HPN), vacuum cleaner (SV/SVT), range/dryer (SRD/SRDT), stage lighting (SC/SCE), and portable power (G/W/PPE). Usage categories: wet/damp locations, oil resistance, temperature ratings. Required by NEC 400.4 for all flexible cord applications.

Note: Multiple tables match 'Table 4': Table 400.4, Table 400.44(B)(1), Table 400.44(B)(2), Table 400.44(B)(3), Table 400.44(B)(4), Table 400.5(A)(1), Table 400.5(A)(2), Table 400.5(A)(3), Table 400.50, Table 400.51(A)(1), Table 400.51(A)(2), Table 400.51(A)(3), Table 402.3, Table 408.5, Table 408.56, Table 424.3, Table 425.3, Table 426.3, Table 427.3, Table 430.10(B), Table 430.12(B), Table 430.12(C)(1), Table 430.22(E), Table 430.23(C), Table 430.247, Table 430.248, Table 430.249, Table 430.250, Table 430.251(A), Table 430.251(B), Table 430.29, Table 430.37, Table 430.5, Table 430.52(C)(1), Table 430.7(B), Table 430.72(B)(2), Table 430.97(D), Table 450.3(A), Table 450.3(B), Table 495.24. Showing Table 400.4. To access others, use specific table ID.

